@node Main
@title "Introduction"

@{b}@{u}Introduction@{ub}@{uu}

 This program is called TrashIt. It is designed to assist you with your Workbench housecleaning needs. If you are tired of selecting `Delete...' or `Empty Trash' from the WorkBench menus, this program will hopefully make life a little easier for you.

 This file contains all of the information contained in the @{" online help " link GeneralControls}, plus additional information that did not belong in any of the online help topics.

	@{" Getting started     " link GettingStarted}
	@{" Overview            " link Overview}
	@{" Options             " link Options}
	@{" Control panel       " link ControlPanel}
	@{" Bug reports         " link Bugs}
	@{" Future enhancements " link Future}
	@{" Beta testers        " link BetaTest}
	@{" Reaching the author " link Author}
	@{" Revision history    " link History}

 This is version 1.20, written by Benbuck Nason on 5.5.93.
@endnode


@node GettingStarted
@title "Getting Started"

@{b}@{u}Getting started@{ub}@{uu}

 @{b}WARNING! This purpose of this program is to delete files. Please use it appropriately.@{ub}

 TrashIt is very versatile, so you can configure it in many ways. Instructions for a few configurations are listed below, but to understand why these configurations work, you should read the section on @{" Options " link Options}. At the very least, you should read the explanation of the @{" EMPTYTIME option " link EMPTYTIME}, because many of the other options depend on how it is set.

 If you just want to try TrashIt out, double click on it's icon. If everything goes well, an @{" AppIcon " link APPICON} will appear. Just drop files onto the @{" AppIcon " link APPICON} and they will be deleted.


 If you want TrashIt to move the files into the Trashcan(s) on your disk(s) and automatically delete them later, follow the steps below.

 1. Double-click on the @{" AppIcon " link APPICON}. This will open the @{" control panel " link ControlPanel}.

 2. Enter a time (in seconds) into the @{" Empty Time gadget " link TrashControls}.

 3. Click on the @{" Close gadget " link GeneralControls}.

 4. Make sure there is a Trashcan on every disk you delete from.


 If you want TrashIt to delete any files you drop directly into the Trashcan on your Work: disk, follow the steps below. If you also want it to wait a little while before it deletes the files in the Trashcan, follow the steps above.

 1. Double-click on the @{" AppIcon " link APPICON}. This will open the @{" control panel " link ControlPanel}.

 2. Enter Work:Trashcan into the @{" Trash Drawer gadget " link TrashControls}.

 3. Click on the @{" Close gadget " link GeneralControls}.


 If you want to change the position of the @{" AppIcon " link APPICON}, follow the steps below.

 1. Double-click on the @{" AppIcon " link APPICON}. This will open the @{" control panel " link ControlPanel}.

 2. Enter the desired position into the @{" Horizontal Position gadget " link AppIconControls} and the @{" Vertical Position gadget " link AppIconControls}.

 3. Click on the @{" Close gadget " link GeneralControls}.
@endnode


@node Overview

@{b}@{u}Overview@{ub}@{uu}

 TrashIt can be run from either a CLI, shell, or Workbench. You do not have to RUN it in order to get your command line back.

 Assuming TrashIt is up-and-running, whenever you want to immediately delete a file or drawer from Workbench, simply drag it onto the TrashIt @{" AppIcon " link APPICON} or @{" AppWindow " link APPWINDOW}, or select the file, then select the @{" AppMenuItem " link APPMENUITEM}. The file or drawer and its icon will be deleted. You can select multiple files or drawers by holding shift while clicking each one individually, or by drag selecting them by clicking outside the icons and dragging the mouse over them.

There two interesting features to TrashIt that didn't really fit anywhere but here: if you use the @{" AppIcon " link APPICON}, @{" AppWindow " link APPWINDOW}, or @{" AppMenuItem " link APPMENUITEM} to delete something and TrashIt moves it into the Trashcan, you can undelete it by opening the Trashcan and deleting the file again. Also, when you delete a disk using the @{" AppIcon " link APPICON}, @{" AppWindow " link APPWINDOW}, or @{" AppMenuItem " link APPMENUITEM}, TrashIt assumes that you want to empty the Trashcan on that disk. If @{" MESSAGES " link MESSAGES} is set to OFF, then it will empty the trash immediately. Otherwise, it will ask you if this is what you want to do, and if you answer `no', then it will ask you if you want to delete all the files on the disk.

 If you decide to change the TrashIt @{" options " link Options}, or if you want to open the @{" AppWindow " link APPWINDOW}, you will need to open the TrashIt @{" control panel " link ControlPanel}. You can do this several ways. You can double click on the @{" AppIcon " link APPICON}, or select the @{" AppMenuItem " link APPMENUITEM} (without having any files selected). You can use the @{" Commodities Exchange " link Commodity} program and select Show. You can use the @{" Commodities Exchange " link Commodity} @{" PopKey " link CX_POPKEY} combination.

 There are several ways to quit TrashIt. You can open the the @{" control panel " link ControlPanel} and click the Quit button, select Quit from the Project menu, or type the letter `Q'. You can use the @{" Commodities Exchange " link Commodity} program and select Kill. You can send it a Control-C from a task management program such as TaskX, ARTM, TaskTool, or Xoper.

 You can also use the @{" Commodities Exchange " link Commodity} program to Enable or Disable TrashIt, which will disable the enable or disable the deletion, but will still allow you to open the @{" control panel " link ControlPanel} and change the options.
@endnode


@node Options

@{b}@{u}Options@{ub}@{uu}

 There are many options recognized by TrashIt, which can be given either on the command line or in the TrashIt icon ToolTypes using the Information... command from the Workbench `Icon' menu. The options are:

	@{" APPICON          " link APPICON}
	@{" APPICONHPOS      " link APPICONHPOS}
	@{" APPICONVPOS      " link APPICONVPOS}
	@{" APPICONNAME      " link APPICONNAME}
	@{" APPICONFILE      " link APPICONFILE}
	@{" FORCE            " link FORCE}
	@{" DELETELIMIT      " link DELETELIMIT}
	@{" EMPTYTIME        " link EMPTYTIME}
	@{" TRASHDRAWER      " link TRASHDRAWER}
	@{" FINDTRASHDRAWERS " link FINDTRASHDRAWERS}
	@{" SOUNDFILE        " link SOUNDFILE}
	@{" APPWINDOW        " link APPWINDOW}
	@{" APPMENUITEM      " link APPMENUITEM}
	@{" APPMENUITEMNAME  " link APPMENUITEMNAME}
	@{" MESSAGES         " link MESSAGES}
	@{" PUBSCREEN        " link PUBSCREEN}
	@{" TOOLPRI          " link TOOLPRI}
	@{" CX_PRIORITY      " link CX_PRIORITY}
	@{" CX_POPKEY        " link CX_POPKEY}
	@{" CX_POPUP         " link CX_POPUP}
	@{" UNIT             " link UNIT}

 These tooltypes should already be present in the TrashIt icon ToolTypes. The DONOTWAIT ToolType should also be present so you can simply copy TrashIt to the WBStartup drawer of your system disk. Note that if you start TrashIt from a CLI or shell, it will only read options from the command line, not from the icon, even if one exists.

 Here is a sample of the options I use and explanations why I use them:

 APPICON=ON
 I want the @{" AppIcon " link APPICON} to be active. 

 APPICONHPOS=620
 Put the @{" AppIcon " link APPICON} at the far right of my screen.

 APPICONVPOS=10
 Put the @{" AppIcon " link APPICON} near the top of my screen.

 APPICONNAME=The Dumper
 Give the @{" AppIcon " link APPICON} a silly name.

 APPICONFILE=Icons/8-Color/3-D Toilet
 Give the @{" AppIcon " link APPICON} a silly icon.

 FORCE=ON
 Override write-protection when deleting.

 DELETELIMIT=5
 Warn me if I try to delete more than 5 files or drawers at one time, and make sure that there are never more than 5 files in a trashcan.

 EMPTYTIME=1800
 Empty the trash every 1800 seconds (30 minutes), not immediately.

 TRASHDRAWER=
 No trash drawer, because I use the standard Trashcans to temporarily hold deleted files.

 FINDTRASHDRAWERS=ON
 Search all disks for Trashcans when TrashIt first starts.

 SOUNDFILE=Sounds/Flush
 Play a silly sound when deleting things.

 APPWINDOW=ON
 Allow the @{" control panel " link ControlPanel} to act as an @{" AppWindow " link APPWINDOW}.

 APPMENUITEM=OFF
 I don't want the @{" AppMenuItem " link APPMENUITEM} to be active.

 APPMENUITEMNAME=
 Since the @{" AppMenuItem " link APPMENUITEM} is off, this is irrelevant.

 MESSAGES=ON
 Talk to me, baby.

 PUBSCREEN=Workbench
 Open @{" control panel " link ControlPanel} on Workbench screen.

 TOOLPRI=0
 Run TrashIt at normal priority.

 CX_PRIORITY=1
 The higher value means that TrashIt will get @{" commodities " link Commodity} events before other @{" commodities " link Commodity}.

 CX_POPKEY=control lshift t
 Key combination to open the @{" control panel " link ControlPanel}.

 CX_POPUP=NO
 Don't open @{" control panel " link ControlPanel} when TrashIt is first started.

 UNIT=0
 Use clipboard unit 0 for {"cut, copy, and paste. " link EditMenu}
@endnode


@node APPICON

@{b}APPICON@{ub}

 This option lets you specify whether or not TrashIt should create an AppIcon, which is an icon on the Workbench screen onto which you can drop files and drawers.

 Example: APPICON=OFF
 Default: APPICON=ON {ON, OFF}

 This corresponds to the @{" On gadget " link AppIconControls} on the @{" control panel " link ControlPanel}.
@endnode

@node APPICONHPOS

@{b}APPICONHPOS@{ub}

 This option lets you specify the x coordinate of the TrashIt @{" AppIcon " link APPICON}. If you don't specify a valid position, or the position you specify is over another icon, the icon will be placed in the next available spot on the screen.

 Example: APPICONHPOS=200
 Default: APPICONHPOS=<None> {An integer}

 This corresponds to the @{" H Position gadget " link AppIconControls} on the @{" control panel " link ControlPanel}.
@endnode

@node APPICONVPOS

@{b}APPICONVPOS@{ub}

 This option lets you specify the y coordinate of the TrashIt @{" AppIcon " link APPICON}. If you don't specify a valid position, or the position you specify is over another icon, the icon will be placed in the next available spot on the screen.

 Example: APPICONVPOS=100
 Default: APPICONVPOS=<None> {An integer}

 This corresponds to the @{" V Position gadget " link AppIconControls} on the @{" control panel " link ControlPanel}.
@endnode

@node APPICONNAME

@{b}APPICONNAME@{ub}

 This option lets you specify the name of the @{" AppIcon " link APPICON}. If you don't specify a value, the name of the icon will be the name of the program (i.e., TrashIt). 

 Example: APPICONNAME=MyTrashCan
 Default: APPICONNAME=<The program's name> {A string}

 This corresponds to the @{" Name gadget " link AppIconControls} on the @{" control panel " link ControlPanel}.
@endnode

@node APPICONFILE

@{b}APPICONFILE@{ub}

 This option lets you specify the icon file that TrashIt will use when it opens the @{" AppIcon " link APPICON}. If you select a valid icon file, that icon's imagery will be used instead of TrashIt's icon or your system's default Trashcan icon.

 Example: APPICONFILE=WORK:Icons/Garbage.info
 Default: APPICONFILE=<None> {A string}

 This corresponds to the @{" File gadget " link AppIconControls} on the @{" control panel " link ControlPanel}.
@endnode

@node FORCE

@{b}FORCE@{ub}

 This option lets you specify whether or not you want TrashIt to force deletions by deprotecting any delete protected files.

 Example: FORCE=ON
 Default: FORCE=OFF {OFF, ON}

 This corresponds to the @{" Force gadget " link TrashControls} on the @{" control panel " link ControlPanel}.
@endnode

@node EMPTYTIME

@{b}EMPTYTIME@{ub}

 This option lets you specify the time, in seconds, that TrashIt will wait before it empties the trash. This is the most important option because many options are dependent on how this is set.

 If you do not specify a time, or if the time is not more than zero seconds, then TrashIt will delete everything immediately when you delete files using the @{" AppIcon " link APPICON}, @{" AppWindow " link APPWINDOW}, or @{" AppMenuItem " link APPMENUITEM}, or when you add a file to the @{" Trash Drawer " link TRASHDRAWER}, if you specified one.

 If you specify a time that is more than zero seconds, then TrashIt will attempt to move files to an appropriate location when you delete them. The locations it looks for are a Trashcan or a @{" Trash Drawer " link TRASHDRAWER} on the disk you are deleting from, in that order.

 Example: EMPTYTIME=180
 Default: EMPTYTIME=0 {An integer}

 This corresponds to the @{" Empty Time gadget " link TrashControls} on the @{" control panel " link ControlPanel}.
@endnode

@node TRASHDRAWER

@{b}TRASHDRAWER@{ub}

 This option lets you specify the name of the drawer to use as an automatic disposal. This option is to allow you to use a drawer other than the Trashcan on your disk to throw trash into. The behavior of this is affected by how @{" EMPTYTIME " link EMPTYTIME} is set.

 Example: TRASHDRAWER=Sys:TrashCan
 Default: TRASHDRAWER=<None> {A string}

 This corresponds to the @{" Trash Drawer gadget " link TrashControls} on the @{" control panel " link ControlPanel}.
@endnode

@node DELETELIMIT

@{b}DELETELIMIT@{ub}

 This option let you specify the maximum number of files that you can delete at one time (through the @{" AppIcon " link APPICON}, @{" AppWindow " link APPWINDOW}, or @{" AppMenuItem " link APPMENUITEM}), without having TrashIt display a warning message.

 It also sets the maximum number of files that are allowed to be in a trashcan at once. For instance if DELETELIMIT is set to 5 and there are 5 files in the trashcan on your Work: disk, when you use TrashIt to delete another file, the oldest file in the trashcan will be deleted and the new file will be moved into the trashcan. For this to happen, @{" EMPTYTIME " link EMPTYTIME} must be greater than zero.

 Example: DELETELIMIT=15
 Default: DELETELIMIT=10 {An integer}

 This corresponds to the @{" Delete Limit gadget " link TrashControls} on the @{" control panel " link ControlPanel}.
@endnode

@node FINDTRASHDRAWERS

@{b}FINDTRASHDRAWERS@{ub}

 This option lets you specify that you want TrashIt to search all your disks for Trashcans to use for automatic disposal. These drawers are the same as the @{" TRASHDRAWER " link TRASHDRAWER}, except that they are found automatically.

 If @{" EMPTYTIME " link EMPTYTIME} is greater than zero and this option is set to OFF, then TrashIt will search for a Trashcan at the time when you delete something. Therefore, the purpose of this option is to allow you to throw files directly into the Trashcan and have TrashIt be notified of this event, so that TrashIt can empty the Trashcan later.

 This option is ignored if @{" EMPTYTIME " link EMPTYTIME} is less than zero.

 Example: FINDTRASHDRAWERS=OFF
 Default: FINDTRASHDRAWERS=ON {ON, OFF}
@endnode

@node SOUNDFILE

@{b}SOUNDFILE@{ub}

 This option lets you specify a sound file that TrashIt will play whenever TrashIt deletes files. If you do not specify a sound file, TrashIt will beep at you when @{" messages " link MESSAGES} are turned off and it deletes something automatically, so that you don't reboot or shut off your computer at that moment.

 Example: SOUNDFILE=Work:Sounds/Warning.snd
 Default: SOUNDFILE=<None> {A string}

 This corresponds to the @{" Sound File gadget " link GeneralControls} on the @{" control panel " link ControlPanel}.
@endnode

@node APPWINDOW

@{b}APPWINDOW@{ub}
 This option lets you specify whether or not you want the TrashIt @{" control panel " link ControlPanel} to also serve as an @{" AppWindow " link APPWINDOW}. This means that you can drop files onto the window and they will be delete. Of course, the @{" control panel " link ControlPanel} must actually be open for you to utilize this.

 Example: APPWINDOW=OFF
 Default: APPWINDOW=ON {ON, OFF}

 This corresponds to the @{" AppWindow gadget " link GeneralControls} on the @{" control panel " link ControlPanel}.
@endnode

@node APPMENUITEM

@{b}APPMENUITEM@{ub}

 This option lets you specify whether or not TrashIt should create an @{" AppMenuItem " link APPMENUITEM}. An AppMenuItem is a menu item that is added to the Tools menu of your Workbench screen. You can use the AppMenuItem to delete files by selecting the files then selecting the AppMenuItem.

 Example: APPMENUITEM=OFF
 Default: APPMENUITEM=ON {ON, OFF}

 This corresponds to the @{" AppMenuItem gadget " link GeneralControls} on the @{" control panel " link ControlPanel}.
@endnode

@node APPMENUITEMNAME

@{b}APPMENUITEMNAME@{ub}

 This option lets you specify the name of the @{" AppMenuItem " link APPMENUITEM}. If you don't specify a value, the name of the menu item will be the same as the @{"AppIcon name " link APPICONNAME}. 

 Example: APPMENUITEMNAME=MyTrashCan
 Default: APPMENUITEMNAME=<The program's name> {A string}
@endnode

@node MESSAGES

@{b}MESSAGES@{ub}

 This option lets you specify whether or not you want TrashIt to display messages and non-fatal errors.

 When this option is OFF, TrashIt may play a @{" sound " link SOUNDFILE} or beep at certain times in order to warn you not to turn off your computer because it is deleting files, or to signal that an error occurred.

 Example: MESSAGES=OFF
 Default: MESSAGES=ON {ON, OFF}

 This corresponds to the @{" Messages gadget " link GeneralControls} on the @{" control panel " link ControlPanel}.
@endnode

@node PUBSCREEN

@{b}PUBSCREEN@{ub}

 This option lets you specify which Public Screen you want the TrashIt @{" control panel " link ControlPanel} to open on.

 Example: PUBSCREEN=Workbench
 Default: PUBSCREEN=<Default public screen> {A string}
@endnode

@node TOOLPRI

@{b}TOOLPRI@{ub}

 This option lets you specify the priority you want TrashIt to run at.

 Example: TOOLPRI=-1
 Default: TOOLPRI=0 {A number}
@endnode

@node CX_PRIORITY

@{b}CX_PRIORITY@{ub}

 This option lets you specify the priority of the TrashIt @{" commodity " link Commodity}.

 Example: CX_PRIORITY=1
 Default: CX_PRIORITY=0 {A number}
@endnode

@node CX_POPKEY

@{b}CX_POPKEY@{ub}

 This option lets you specify a @{" commodities " link Commodity} hotkey to pop open the TrashIt @{" control panel " link ControlPanel}.

 Example: CX_POPKEY="control lalt b"
 Default: CX_POPKEY="control lshift t" (Control + Left-Shift + t) {A string}

 This corresponds to the @{" CX PopKey gadget " link GeneralControls} on the @{" control panel " link ControlPanel}.
@endnode

@node CX_POPUP

@{b}CX_POPUP@{ub}

 This option lets you specify whether or not TrashIt should open the @{" control panel " link ControlPanel} when it starts.

 Example: CX_POPUP=NO
 Default: CX_POPUP=YES {YES, NO}
@endnode

@node UNIT

@{b}UNIT@{ub}

 This option lets you specify the clipboard unit number to use for cut, copy, and paste.

Example: UNIT=1
Default: UNIT=0 {A number}
@endnode


@node ControlPanel
@title "Control Panel"

@{b}@{u}Control Panel@{ub}@{uu}

 The control panel is what allows you to easily configure the TrashIt @{" options " link Options} to suit your personal preferences. The control panel is a window with gadgets that enable you to modify the settings that TrashIt is currently using. It also has menus for some of the options.

	@{" AppIcon Controls" link AppIconControls}
	@{" Trash Controls  " link TrashControls}
	@{" General Controls" link GeneralControls}
	@{" Edit Menu       " link EditMenu}

 Almost all of the Control Panel gadgets and menu items have corresponding @{" options " link Options}, so for a complete description of the item, refer to the that option.
@endnode


@node AppIconControls
@title "AppIcon Controls"

@{b}@{u}AppIcon Controls@{ub}@{uu}

 The AppIcon is an icon on the Workbench screen onto which you can drop files and drawers to be deleted. You can also double click on the AppIcon to open the TrashIt @{" control panel " link ControlPanel}.

 @{b}Horizontal Position@{ub}
 This corresponds to the @{" APPICONHPOS " link APPICONHPOS} option.

 @{b}Vertical Position@{ub}
 This corresponds to the @{" APPICONVPOS " link APPICONVPOS} option.

 @{b}On@{ub}
 This corresponds to the @{" APPICON " link APPICON} option.

 @{b}Name@{ub}
 This corresponds to the @{" APPICONNAME " link APPICONNAME} option.

 @{b}File@{ub}
 This corresponds to the @{" APPICONFILE " link APPICONFILE} option.

 @{b}Select File@{ub}
 This will bring up a file requester to allow you to choose an icon file for the AppIcon. Refer to the @{" APPICONFILE " link APPICONFILE} option for more information. For this option to be available, you must have the ASL library.
@endnode


@node TrashControls
@title "Trash Controls"

@{b}@{u}Trash Controls@{ub}@{uu}

 Trash refers to the files and drawers in the @{" Trash Drawer(s) " link TRASHDRAWER}.

 @{b}Empty Time@{ub}
 This corresponds to the @{" EMPTYTIME " link EMPTYTIME} option.

 @{b}Delete Limit@{ub}
 This corresponds to the @{" DELETELIMIT " link DELETELIMIT} option.

 @{b}Force@{ub}
 This corresponds to the @{" FORCE " link FORCE} option.

 @{b}Trash Drawer@{ub}
 This corresponds to the @{" TRASHDRAWER " link TRASHDRAWER} option.

 @{b}Select Trash Drawer@{ub}
 This will bring up a file requester to allow you to choose a Trash Drawer. Refer to the @{" TRASHDRAWER " link TRASHDRAWER} for more information. For this option to be available, you must have the ASL library.

 @{b}SoundFile@{ub}
 This corresponds to the @{" SOUNDFILE " link SOUNDFILE} option.

 @{b}Select Sound File@{ub}
 This will bring up a file requester to allow you to choose a sound file. Refer to the @{" SOUNDFILE " link SOUNDFILE} for more information. For this option to be available, you must have the ASL library.
@endnode


@node GeneralControls
@title "General Controls"

@{b}@{u}General Controls@{ub}@{uu}

 These are the general controls.

 @{b}AppWindow@{ub}
 This corresponds to the @{" APPWINDOW " link APPWINDOW} option.

 @{b}AppMenuItem@{ub}
 This corresponds to the @{" APPMENUITEM " link APPMENUITEM} option.

 @{b}Messages@{ub}
 This corresponds to the @{" MESSAGES " link MESSAGES} option.

 @{b}Help@{ub}
 This gives brief explanatory messages such as this one. Select the Help gadget, menu item, or key to enter and exit help mode. While in help mode, select any gadget or menu item to see a message like this one.

 There is also `Menu Help' available. To use Menu Help, you do not have to be in help mode. Just highlight the menu item you wish to get help on, and simultaneously press the help key.

 @{b}CxPopKey@{ub}
 This corresponds to the @{" CX_POPKEY " link CX_POPKEY} option.

 @{b}Close@{ub}
 This will close the TrashIt @{" control panel " link ControlPanel}, but will not cause TrashIt to quit.

 @{b}Save{ub}
 This will save the current TrashIt settings to the TrashIt icon ToolTypes, after displaying a requester verifying that you did not select Save accidentally.

 @{b}About@{ub}
 This will give you a brief introductory message describing TrashIt. It will also tell you the version number.

 @{b}Quit@{ub}
 This quits TrashIt.
@endnode


@node EditMenu
@title "Edit Menu"

@{b}@{u}Edit Menu@{ub}@{uu}

 The Edit menu functions are only available when the currently selected gadget contains text or numbers that you can edit. Cut, Copy, and Paste all read or write to or from the clipboard.

 @{b}Cut@{ub}
 This will copy the contents of the current gadget to the clipboard, then remove the gadget's contents.

 @{b}Copy@{ub}
 This will copy the contents of the current gadget to the clipboard.

 @{b}Paste@{ub}
 This will paste the contents of the clipboard into the currently selected gadget. Trashit will attempt to insert the clip into the gadget at the current cursor position.

 Be aware that this can be awkward for number gadgets with contents that are negative and/or a clip that is negative. This is due to the possibility of inappropriate placement of minus signs. If TrashIt detects that these conditions exist, it will completely replace the contents of the current gadget with the contents of the clipboard.

 @{b}Erase@{ub}
 This will remove the contents of the currently selected gadget.
@endnode


@node Commodity

@{b}@{u}Commodity@{ub}@{uu}

 If, possible, TrashIt installs itself as a commodity. This allows you to easily control it using the Commodities Exchange (CX) program that came with your system disks.

 If you open the Commodites Exchange window, there will be a list of all the commodities currently installed on your system. If you find `TrashIt' in the list and click on on it, you will be able to use the rest of the CX gadgets to control TrashIt.

 There are also several @{" options " link Options} and a @{" control panel " link ControlPanel} gadget that let you control the TrashIt commodity:

	@{" CX_PRIORITY option " link CX_PRIORITY}
	@{" CX_POPKEY option   " link CX_POPKEY}
	@{" CX_POPUP option    " link CX_POPUP}
	@{" CxPopKey gadget    " link GeneralControls}
@endnode


@node Bugs

@{b}@{u}Bugs@{ub}@{uu}

 There are no known bugs in TrashIt.

 It has been @{" beta tested " link BetaTest} on various machines (500, 1000, 2000, 1500, 3000, 4000) and operating systems (2.04, 2.1, 3.0, 3.1).

 Please cease to use TrashIt if you notice any strange behavior, and PLEASE @{" report " link Author} any bugs you find. I really hope you don't unintentionally delete any files because of this program. Please don't use it if you do not have backup copies of all your files. Rest assured, though, that I use this program constantly, so I will (hopefully) find and fix any bugs that may exist.

 You can send bug reports or @{" enhancement requests " link Future} through @{" regular mail " link Author} or @{" email " link Author}.
@endnode

@node Author
@title "Reaching the Author"

@{b}@{u}Reaching the Author@{ub}@{uu}

 You can reach me (Benbuck Nason) at the following places:

